== Australian Market Context

=== Regulatory Environment

ECM transactions in Australia governed by:
- *ASX Listing Rules*: Admission requirements, capital raising rules, disclosure obligations
- *ASIC Regulatory Guides*: RG 228 (Prospectuses), RG 254 (Offering securities under a disclosure document)
- *Corporations Act*: Capital raising provisions, disclosure requirements, liability framework
- *Takeovers Panel*: Oversight of equity transactions that may trigger takeover obligations

=== Market Dynamics

Australian ECM market characterized by:
- Strong IPO market for mid-cap companies (AU\$100m-1bn market cap)
- Active secondary market (placements, rights issues, SPPs)
- Concentration of boutique advisory capability in Sydney
